Series following the lives of rural vets as they treat all creatures great and small.
 
 
 
[b]1/15 In Teesdale, farm vet Richard helps a sheep who has mysteriously gone blind.

2/15 A labrador gun dog is rushed to small animal vet Steve after being accidentally shot.

3/15 Equine vet Kerry treats a critically ill miniature donkey foal.
 
4/15 Small animal vet Adam decides his much-loved shetland pony Hector needs a major operation. 
 
5/15 Richard visits a long-standing client where he de-horns a cow and trims a cow's hoof [/b]
 
6/15 Adam deals with an emergency at the small animal hospital when a dog is hit by a train. 
 
7/15 Farm vet Richard finds out how many of farmer Cliff's cows are pregnant.

8/15 Equine vet Sybil attempts a delicate operation to save a horse's sight in Teesdale.

9/15 Vet Megan is on a mission in Fife to help re-home 80 commercial caged hens.
 
10/15 Vet Steve helps a kestrel with a damaged wing and hopes to release her back to the wild.
